comments: Drilled and oriented 12 1/4" hole section from 2575 m to 2579 m MD. Drilling parameters : 3000 lpm / SPP~160 bar / 80 rpm / Torque~16 kNm / WOB 1-3 MT. Controlled ROP to 2 m/hrs (time drililling). Routed returns to bigbag/IBC due to washout in DCI piping.

Drilled and oriented 12 1/4" section from 2579 m to 2585 m MD. Drilling parameters : 3000 lpm / SPP ~157 bar / 130 rpm / Torque ~18 kNm / WOB ~2 MT. Controlled ROP to 2 m/hrs (time drililling). Routed returns to skips due to washout in DCI low pressure piping.

Pulled back into at 2545 m MD. As permitted by weather condtions, performed ciritical maintenance of TDS and PRS. Disconnected hose on cement standpipe for troubleshooting blockage on hose. Meanwhile perfomed cleaning of DCI mill tank.
Excess time used on service on TDS and PRS. RIH to TD at 2585 m MD.

Downlinked Powerdrive. Drilled and oriented 12 1/4" section from 2585 m to 2590 m MD. Drilling parameters : 3000 lpm / SPP ~160 bar / 130 rpm / Torque ~20 kNm / WOB ~1-5 MT / ECD 1,28. Controlled ROP to 10 m/hrs as dictated logistic challenges / weather conditions. Meanwhile performed cleaning/repairs in DCI system.

Drilled and oriented 12 1/4" hole section from 2590 m to 2663 m MD. Drilling parameters : 3000 lpm / SPP ~160 bar / 80-130 rpm / Torque 20-24 kNm / WOB 2-7 MT / ECD 1,29. Stepped up ROP in incrememts from 10 to 25 m/hrs as dictated by cuttings handling.
At 2663 m MD, got problems with Powerdrive - not able to maintain toolface/steering. Pulled out to 2654 m MD and downinked Powerdrive in attempt to regain steering.
Drilled ahead to 2665 m MD - prevailing problems in maintaining toolface with Powerdrive.
Reciprocated on stand whilst discussing situation with town. Decided to POOH to change Powerdrive.
Flow checked well prior to POOH - well static.
Pumped 5 m3 1,57 sg slug. Allowed mud level to settle.
POOH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 2565 m to 2464 m MD. Open hole tripping speed 200 m/hrs.
POOH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 2464 m to 609 m MD. Tripping speed 1280 m/hrs.
Flowchecked prior to pulling BHA - well static. Observed slack hoist wire on PRS.
Troubleshot slack wire on PRS. Found mismatch on tension cyclinders - rectified problem.
POOH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" HWDP from 609 m to 107 m MD.
Held toolbox talk for installing bushings.
Removed auto slips. Installed masterbushing and bowl.
POOH with 12 1/4" BHA. Racked back BHA in derrick. Broke out powerdrive. Broke bit using rig tongs.
Laid down Powerdrive. Picked up back-up Powerdrive. Made up 12 1/4" bit. Hung off powedrive in rotary.
Made up and RIH with 12 1/4" BHA to 107 m MD.
Removed masterbushing. Installed auto slips.
RIH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" HWDP/DP from 107 m to 606 m MD.
Fiilled pipe and  performed shallow test of Powerdrive and MWD - ok. Performed kick-drill.
RIH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 606 m to 1697 m MD. Filled pipe every 500 m tripping in. Tripping speed 545 mhrs.
RIH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 1697 m to 2626 m MD. Filled pipe every 500 m. Tripping speed 465 m/hrs.
Made up TDS. Washed down last stand at 2000 lpm / SPP 80 bar.

Drilled and oriented 12 1/4" hole section from 2665 m to 2755 m MD. Downlinked Powerdrive and took surveys at connections as instructed by DD/MWD. Drilling parameters : 3200 lpm / SPP ~180 bar / 65-130 rpm / Torque 18-24 kNm / WOB 2-8 MT / ECD 1,28. Linited ROP to 10 m/hrs due limited processing capacity and ongoing work on DCI. Full capacity of DCI regained at 18:00.

Drilled and oriented 12 1/4" hole section from 2745 m to 2790 m MD. Drilling prameters : 3200-3400 lpm / SPP 175-195 bar / 130 rpm / Torque 18-24 kNm / WOB 2-9 MT / ECD 1,27. ROP 3-8 m/hrs as determined by geology. Experienced high stick/slip and low ROP from ~2770 m MD (Ekofisk). 100% limestone shows at 2780 m MD. Performed kick drill.

Drilled and oriented 12 1/4" hole section from 2790 m to 2818 m MD. Drilling parameters 3400 lpm / SPP ~180 bar / 130-160 rpm / Torque 20-26 kNm / WOB 5-9 MT / ECD 1,27. ROP 2-8 m/hrs as determined by geology. Experienced high stick/slip when drilling chalk.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2818 m to 2853 m MD. Drilling parameters : 3400 lpm / SPP ~194 bar / 150-180 rpm / Torque 23-29 kNm / WOB 10-12 MT / ECD 1,27. ROP 3-8 m/hrs as determined by geology and stick/slip. Lost return flow and standpipe pressure.

Observed lost return to pit and falling standpipe pressure. Picked off bottom and reciprocated stand from 2827 m to 2841 m MD / 10 rpm.  No drop in active, annulus full, i.e. no downhole losses detected. Ivestigated situation. Inspected lines from pit to TDS, found no leakages. Closed IBOP and attmepted to pump, found that problem was related to the surface system.

Lined up cement unit to circulate on well. Circulated in well at set intervalls using cement unit pumping at 1200 lpm / SPP 26 bar. Reciprocated stand and rotated 10 rpm. Monitoed well on trip tank when not pumping - well static. Performed troubleshooting on pumps and circulation system.

Found likely cause of problem to be blocked splitter valve in suction module. Not able to use pit#7 as active pit. Lined up to pump from pit #15 taking retuns to pit #15 and #7 and used mixpump for levelling the two pits. Stepped up pumprate to 3400 lpm and RIH to 2853 m MD.
Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2853 m to 2865 m MD. Drilling parameters : 3400 lpm / SPP ~194 bar / 150-180 rpm / Torque 24-27 kNm / WOB 6-8 MT / ECD 1,28. ROP 2-6 m/hrs as determined by geology.
Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2865 m to 2896 m MD. Drilling parameters : 3400 lpm / SPP ~198 bar / 150-180 rpm / Torque 24-27 kNm / WOB 6-8 MT / ECD 1,28. ROP 4-7 m/hrs as determined by geology.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole from 2896 m to section TD at 2920 m MD. Drilling parameters : 3400 lpm / SPP ~195 bar / 180 rpm / Torque 28-32 kNm / WOB 3-5 MT / ECD 1,28. ROP 4-7 m/hrs as determined by geology.
Circulated hole clean prior to POOH, reciprocated string between 2920 m and 2908 m MD. Parameters : 3400 lpm / SPP ~199 bar / 150 rpm / Torque 22-26 kNm / ECD 1,28.
Flow checked well - static.

Broke off TDS. Dropped gyro. Made ut TDS and pumped gyro down string. Observed mud leakage from TDS, washpipe leaking. Pumped 5 m3 1,55 sg slug. Performed rotational gyro survey as instucted by Gyrodata.
POOH with 12 1/4" BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 2904 m to 2545 m MD.
Secured well with kelly cock-. Lowered TDS work platform. Changed washpipe. Installed test swadge on TDS.
Tested washpipe and standpipe to 345 bar / 10 min - ok. Broke swadge.
Filled trip tanks. POOH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 2545 m to 1132 m MD. Tripping speed 565 m/hrs. Meanwhile mounted riser cradles and laid out casing.
POOH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 1132 m to 109 m MD. Tripping speed 455 m/hrs. Meanwhile mounted riser cradles and lifted riser tension jonit / pup joint to cradle.
Flowchecked prior to pulling BHA - well static. Checked dies on PRS. Held toolbox talk for manual handling. Removed PS-21 auto slips. Installed masterbushing and bowls.

POOH with 12 1/4" BHA from 109 m MD to surfcae. Broke stand of 5 1/2" HWDP for acccess to gyro. Retrieved gyro. Made up HWDP stand and racked back same. Broke and racked back jar/DC stand in derrick. Broke and laid out 2 ea NMDC. Broke and laid out ARC, MWD and Powerdrive Xceeed.
Cleared and tided drilfloor. Lifted BHAs to baskets on maindeck.
RIH with 9 5/8" 53,5# 13Cr80 VamTop HCNA casing from 300 m to 357 m MD. Installed centralizers. Filled casing every 5th joint with OBM.
Held toolbox talk / handover meeting.
RIH with 9 5/8" 53,5# 13Cr80 VamTop HCNA casing from 357 m to 460 m MD. Installed centralizers. Filled casing every 5th joint.
RIH with 9 5/8" 53,5# 13Cr 80 VamTop HCNA casing from 460 m to 714 m MD. Filled casing every 5th joint with OBM.
Rejected make-up of joint #47. Broke out joint - inspected and found damage on pin and box threads. Laid out joint #47. Broke and laid out joint #48.
RIH with 9 5/8" 53,5# 13Cr 80 VamTop HCNA casing from 702 m to 783 m MD. A 9 5/8" joint unexpectedly tilted off of the HTS roller section.

Held time out for safety and troubleshoting after a 9 5/8" casing joint was driven off of the HTS power rollers. Made up and ran 9 5/8" casing joint on HTS, installed swadge and kelly cock. Investigated incident. The 9 5/8" was tilted resting on the roller frame and the deck. The area in which the casing joint tilted was barriered off according to standard procedure for running HTS/PDM. Revised practice for picking up casing until further notice, i.e. only one joint on HTS rollers and HTS at the time.
Held toolbox talk for continued casing running.
RIH with 9 5/8" 53,5# 13Cr 80 VamTop HCNA casing from 795 m to 1113 m MD. Filled casing every 10th joint with OBM.

Dressed PDM for picking up 10 3/4" casing. Changed to 10 3/4" BX4 elevator. Changed inserts in PS-21. Dressed tong for 10 3/4" casing. Moved roller section from forward to aft cantilever. Made up 10 3/4" swadge to kelly cock. Moved redundant 9 5/8" casing to fwd stb bay. Counted 9 5/8" joints left on deck, 37 - ok.
Made up 9 5/8" x 10 3/4 x-over. RIH with 10 3/4" 60,7# 13Cr80 VamTop casing from 1113 m to 1580 m MD. Filled every 10th casing joint with OBM.
Held toolbox talk / handover meeting.
RIH with 10 3/4" 60,7# 13Cr80 VamTop casing from 1700 m to 2001 m MD. Filled every 5th casing joint with OBM.
Removed power rollers on cantilever. Cleared excess equipment from drillfloor prior to running casing stands from derrick.
Held toolbox talk prior to running 10 3/4" casing stands.
Attempted to latch BX elevator onto casing stand in PRS - negative. Troubleshot. Decided to change to spider elevator.
Rigged down BX4 elevator and bails. Rigged up 15 ft bails. Made up FAC tool to TDS. Installed and hooked up spider elevator.
Function tested spider elevator. Observed air supply problem from TDS. Troubleshot problem. Changed 2 way pneumatic valve on TDS.
Held toolbox talk for running 10 3/4" casing stands.
RIH with 10 3/4" casing stands from 2001 m to 2560 m MD. Filled every stand with OBM.

Stabbed 10 3/4" FAC packer into casing with 8 MT setdown. Commenced pumping, mud sprayed accross packer, not holding pressure. Set down 15 MT on FAC packer. Stepped up rate to 1330 lpm / SPP 31 bar. Circulated for 10 min, stable pressure and no losses. Took up/down weights 256/199 MT.
RIH with 10 3/4" casing stands from 2560 m to 2770 m MD. No significant drag in open hole (max 5 MT). Filled every stand with OBM.
Held toolbox talk for rigging down equipment.

Removed PS-21 slips and installed masterbushing. Rigged down FAC tool. Rigged down spider elevator. Removed 15 ft bails and installed standard bails. Installed and hooked up DP elevator and link tilt. Counted 10 3/4" joints on deck, 9 ea - ok.
Picked up 10 3/4" casing hanger with elevator and tugger. Made up 10 3/4" casing hanger. Checked casing hanger according to Vetco procedure.
Ran 10 3/4" casing hanger below rotary and hung off on slips. Rigged down casing tong.
Rigged dowm and removed Odfjell casing tong.
Held toolbox talk / handover meeting.
Removed excess casing handling equipment from drillfloor.
RIH with 9 5/8" x 10 3/4" casing on 5 1/2" HWDP from 2779 m to 2911 m MD. No siginificant drag in well. Filled pipe with OBM.
Connected hydraulic control lines and cement hose to cement head. Picked up and made up cement head. Made up cement hose to manifold outlet. Hooked up valve control panel. Made up TDS to cement head.
Staged up pumps in 200 lpm increments to 1500 lpm / SPP 57 bar. Washed down from 2911 m to 2915 m MD. Landed 10 3/4" hanger at 140,1 m MD and set down 5 MT. Verified measurements and set down 120 MT.
Circulated bottoms up at 1500 lpm / SPP 57 bar. Meanwhile held toolbox talk for cement job.
Lined up to cement unit. Pressure tested cement line and hose against lo-torq on cement head - 345 bar / 10 min - ok.
Pumped 8 m3 of base oil at 1500 lpm / SPP 42 bar.
Pumped 19 m3 1,3 sg cement spacer at 500 lpm and chased same with 2,5 m3 OBM. Released lower dart.
Mixed and pumped 1,9 sg silica cement at 800 lpm / CUP~55 bar. After pumping approx 15 m3 got problems with bulk transfer, not able to transfer from bulk tank#10 to surge tank.
Troubleshot bulk transfer system. Pressured up on bulk tank#9. Meanwhile pumped cement at slow rate.
Transferred cement from bulk tank #9 to surge tank. Mixed and pumped rest of cement, in total 21,2 m3 1,9 sg silica cement.
Displaced cement line partly with 500 l drillwater. Released upper dart and pumped another 1500 l drillwater from cement unit.

Lined up to use rigpumps for displacement. Zeroed stroke counter. Displaced cement at 1500 lpm / SPP 25-85 bar. Reduced pumprate to 1000 lpm after pumping 5288 strokes. Bumped plug after 5428 strokes with 147 bar (FCP 70 bar). Pump efficiency 96,7 %.

Closed IBOP and lined over to cement unit. Equalised across lo-torq with 160 bar. Pressured up to test casing 345 bar / 10 min. Observed pressure increasing 3 bar over 10 min due to thermal expansion of mud.

Bled back to cement unit to check for backflow. Bled back 2,2 m3 OBM. Observed pressure increase of 0,5 bar / min when shutting in. Bled back and measured return rate to 1,5 l/min. Suspected small leak across float valves.

Pressured up to 50 bar in order to equalise u-tube pressure from cement coulmn and stop back flow. Closed lo-torqe valve on cement head and disconnected cement hose. Flushed surfaced lines. Connected cement hose to cement head.
Equlalised across lo-torque valve on cement head with 60 bar. Opened lo-torq and read 71 bar in well. Bled back 650 liter, no continued backflow observed.

Disconnected cement hose and hydraulic control lines. Released PADPRT from 10 3/4" casing hanger with 8 clockwise turns. Pulled back to 137 m MD, broke and laid down cement head. Dropped 2 ea sponge balls, wiped and cleaned string pumping at 3300 lpm / SPP 33 bar for 10 min.
Laid out 2 ea 5 1/2" HWDP singles. POOH with PADPRT on 5 1/2" HWDP to surface. Broke and laid out PADPRT.
Made up setting tool / 10 3/4" lock down sub. RIH with lock down sub on 5 1/2" DP from surface to 87 m MD.
RIH with lock down with lock down sub from 86 m to 140 m MD. Set lock down sub according to Vetco precdure. Pull tested lock down sub with 50 MT overpull - ok.
POOH with lock down sub setting tool from 140 m MD to surface. Laid down setting tool.
RIH with 6 stand of 5 1/2" HWDP from surface to 226 m MD. Made up 10 3/4" RTTS. RIH with RTTS to ~319 m MD.
Made up TDS, Set RTTS by clockwise rotation and set down 20 MT. RTTS set with mid packer element at ~319 m MD.
Lined up from cement unit to pump through TDS. Put 10 bar pressure on IBOP, opened same and verified line-up. Pressure tested RTTS and casing below to 210 bar / 10 min - 0,3% drop - ok.
Released from RTTS according to Halliburton procedure. Picked up to 313 m MD. Pressured up to 30 bar above RTTS.

Pressure tested RTTS / 10 3/4" casing above and cement in 9 5/8" x 13 3/8" annulus. Pressured up in 30 bar increments. Pressure dropped 1,5-2,5 bar / 10 min at 30, 60, 90 and 120 bar -  but with improving trends towards end of each test. Continued to pressure up to 150, 180 and 210 bar and observed continued improving trend. Obtained test 210 bar / 10 min with 0,9 bar drop (0,42%) - ok. Bled off pressure and opened pipe ram. RIH with RTTS stinger to 314 m MD.
Staged up pumps and circulated bottoms up at 2000 lpm / SPP 9 bar.
Displaced from OBM to seawater above RTTS pumping at 2000 lpm / SPP 13-6 bar. Pumped in total in total 76 m3 seawter. Routed contamianted returns to pits. Flushed choke and kill lines with seawater.
Spotted 5 m3 hivis on top of RTTS.

POOH with RTTS setting tool on 5 1/2" DP from 314 m to 46 m MD. Rigged up air line to choke manifold. Closed upper pipe tram. Purged air trhough choke/kill line taking returns via hose to mudbucket drain. Repeated purging.
POOH with RTTS setting tool from 46 m MD to surface. Broke and laid out tool. Cleared and tidied drillfloor.
Held toolboox talk prior to nippling diverter and BOP.
Rigged up long sling in TDS. Pulled diverter and set back on drillfloor.
Broke overshot connection on BOP. Pulled and set back overshot.
Nippled down BOP. Unable to break NT-2 studs on connector, adjusted BOP trolley accordingly. Not able to run BOP trolley due to hydraulic oil overheating.
Troubleshot problem with hydraulic oil overheating. Ran other hydraulic equipment to cool hydraulic oil in main system.
Continued to nipple BOP connector. Could not break NT-2 studs, adjusted BOP trolley accordingly. Overtorqued and broke 1" x 3/4" x-over from j-gun to socket.
Searched rig for spare x-over / socket. Welded 1,5" hex socket onto 1" drive interface on j-gun. Meanwhile positioned Claxton tool and brought riser spider to drillfloor.
Broke NT-2 connector on BOP.
Broke NT-2 connector on BOP. Moved BOP to stb side using trolley. Landed BOP on stump.

Removed long slings from TDS. Installed bails and elevator. Removed master outer ring and master bushing. Ran Claxton tool through rotary using tugger. Installed outer ring and master bushing. Hung off Claxton tool on pup joint.
Made up stand of 5 1/2" DP to Claxton tool. Ran in with Claxton tool and landed same onto BOP joint.
Made up studs on Claxton tool to 3300 ft lbs.
Made up studs on Claxton tool to 3300 ft lbs.
Bled of hydraulic pressure on tension cylinders and transferred 60 MT tension to block. Retracted tension cylinders.
Dismantled contact ring and tensioner assembly. Removed centralizer in Centralizer deck. Landed tension ring on vinyl guide. Inserted wooden chuks in deck openings.
Rigged down scaffolding on Weather deck. Ran tugger line to seabed and attached same, ran hotstab to seabed. Issued instruction for shut-in on wells F-14, F-4 and F-5.
Pulled dummy hotstab and engaged hotstab in TBC using ROV.
Waited on production to shut in and bleed off wells F-14, F-4 and F-5.

Adjusted blockweight to 110 MT / set down 20 MT. Applied 3000 psi unlock pressure to TBC. Observed indicator movement on ROV. Pulled riser free of wellhead in one continuous stroke. Pulled out and hung off in slips on Claxton pup joint.
Broke stand of 5 1/2" DP from Clacton tool. Made up stand of 5 1/2" DP to production riser running tool and racked back in derrick.
Removed master bushing and outer ring.

Held toolbox talk for installing riser spider. Splitted, installed , hooked up and functioned riser spider. Pull out with HPDR to upper pup / tension joint connection. Removed fairings, hung off riser in spider.
Removed thread protectors. Broke flange according to Vetco procedure using Bandak bolt tensioner tools.
Laid out 1st double with simultaneous lift by block and deck crane. Adjusted slings to balance lift. Laid 1st double on riser m/u cradle.

Pull out with HPDR 2nd double "D" "and hung off in riser spider. Removed fairings. Removed thread protectors. Broke flange according to Vetco procedure using Bandak bolt tensioner tools. Made up handling flange type C using j-gun.
Laid out 2nd double "D"  by simultaneous lift by block and deck crane. Laid 2nd double in port riser rack.

Pull out with HPDR 3rd double "C" and hung off in riser spider. Removed fairings. Removed thread protectors. Broke flange according to Vetco procedure using Bandak bolt tensioner tools. Made up handling flange type C using j-gun.
Laid out 3rd double "C" by simultaneous lift by block and deck crane. Laid 3rd double in port riser rack.

Pull out with HPDR 4th double "B" and hung off in riser spider. Removed fairings. Removed thread protectors. Broke flange according to Vetco procedure using Bandak bolt tensioner tools. Made up handling flange type C using j-gun.
Laid out 4th double "B" by simultaneous lift by block and deck crane. Laid 4th double in port riser rack.
Pulled out with HPDR 5th double "A" (singel/stress/TBC).
Laid out 5th double "A" by simultaneous lift by block and deck crane. Laid 5th double in port riser rack.
Cleared and tidied drillfloor and wellhead. Covered hatch on Centralizer deck. Prepeared for transferring tension cylinders to Centralizer deck.

Waited on weather to run production riser.

Meanwhile :
-Brought thension cylinders to Centralizer deck
-Replaced tension cylinders
-Changed wire on drillfoor yellow and black tugger
-Trobleshot HTS - no clear fault indication - random behaviour at w.r.t. stop point
-Performed maintenance of drawwork
-Emptied pit #5 into skips

-Removed riser spider and installed master bushings to access iron roughneck.
-Started to disassemble aft iron roughneck.

Meanwhile :
-Instructed used of deluge/foam system on wellhead to crew as a part off weekly drill.
-Pressure tested BOP on stump. Ok.
-Disassembled and moved aft iron roughneck.
-Disconnected fwd iron roughneck and moved to aft position.

-Worked on motor for slurry pump.

-Built scaffolding/barriers around deck openings.
Held tool box talk for running production riser and hot-stab with involved personnel.

Lifted TBC/stress joint from cantiliver until handling sub was latched into TDS. Unhooked uppermost sling and lifted TBC/stress joint with TDS until it was hanging vertically. Lifted hot-stab to drill floor.

Meanwhile installed VX-ring using ROV.
Function tested TBC according to Vetco instructions.
Function tested TBC according to Vetco instructions.

Waited on weather to run production riser. Informed Production to shut down F-4, F-5 and F-14 at 08:10.

Meanwhile :
-Performed rig maintenace
-Routed tuggers to guide TBC/production riser.

Held tool box talk prior to running production riser. Lowered TBC/stress joint through rotary. Extended riser spider dogs and installed stop bolts in PR holes #3. Hung off stress joint in riser spider. Alligned TBC ROV panels and checked TBC connector for damage.
Lifted 1st double with dual lift on block and deckcrane.

Disconnected handling tool. Made up flanged connection according to Vetco/Bandak procedure. Installed fairring on coupling. Ran in and placed TBC connector in level with Weather deck deck. Prepared guidewires in slot F-10. Ran and attched 10 MT guide wire to template. Attempted to run 6 MT guidewire, but the wire tangled around 10 MT tugger wire and slipped out of ROV hook assy, due to high winds. Waves had increased to 4-6 m and operation was stopped. Hung off PR in riser spider and kept TDS engaged to handling tool.

-Cleaned lower shakers
-Recovered moonpool 10 MT tugger from seabed
-Held tool box meeting for untangeling guide wires and running PR
POOH 5-10 m with PR. Untangled 6 mT guide wire and hot-stab rope. Disconnected guide wire clamp from TBC. RIH and hung off PR in riser spider.

Removed handling tool. Lifted 2nd double to drillfloor with dual lift on block and deck crane. MU up flanged connection according to Vetco/Bandak procedure. Tested flanges to 3000 psi / 5 min,  ok. RIH with PR from 37 m to 66 m through splash zone.

Removed handling tool. Lifted 4nd double to drillfloor with dual lift on block and deck crane. MU up flanged connection according to Vetco/Bandak procedure. Tested flange to 3000 psi / 5 min,  ok. RIH with PR from 66 m to 118 m t.

Removed handling tool. Lifted tension joint double to drillfloor with dual lift on block and deck crane. MU up flanged connection according to Vetco/Bandak procedure. Attempted to pressure test flange to 3000 psi / 5 min.
Pumped up pressure several times to obtain good test on tension joint double flange. Tested flanges to 3000 psi / 5 min, ok.
Held tool box talk with new crew prior to RIH with PR. RIH with tension joint double and landed off in riser spider.
Removed handling tool from riser tension joint. Observed lateral movement on flange studs. Verified with town prior to continued operation.

Bled down WHP f/ 95bar to zero. Total volume bled back 1,56 m3.

RIH w/ run #1  5,75" OD drift from surface to 3070 m taking returns via KWV and choke to t/t.
Observed resistance while passing ASV and DHG.
POOH w/ drift run from 3070 m to surface.
Pulled tool into catcher, lined up to leak test XMT cross to 70 bar with cement unit.

Leak tested Xmas tree to 70 bar.
Lined up and displaced OBM from riser to trip tank using nitrogen.

Broke out lubricator, cleaned and L/O toolstring.
L/O lubricator to HTS.
Changed grease injection head and sheaves from S/L to 5/16" e-line. Re-arranged wireline skid. Installed and calibrated SLB depth counter.
P/U lubricator and M/U same. Lined up to test rig-up via KWV and tree. Tested lubricator and W/L riser to 30/200 bar for 5/10 min.

Broke out lubricator. P/U and M/U toolstring for run #2 (EVO plug). 
Stabbed lubricator and M/U QTS. Leak tested QTS to 200 bar 10 min.
Opened SV and HMV.

RIH w/ run #2 (EVO) 5,72" OD plug from surface to 3030 m.
Worked toolstring through ASV (FLX-4) at 495 m.

Leak tested across Xmas tree to 70 bar for 10 min.
Flushed wireline riser and lubricator with nitrogen. Broke out lubricator.
L/D toolstring.
Pressured tested EVO plug to 20/240 bar for 5/10 min. Pumped and bled back 932 l.

R/D lubricator. Re-configured AWS winch. Hooked up add-on drum with 7-46 SLB cable. Calibrated weight cell and installed depth counter. 

Meanwhile isolated rigfloor equipment. Changed out oil on TDS.
Cleared pipe deck to L/O 3 1/2" DP. Installed new cladding on drag chain.

Installed AWS pump in sub on W/L riser, connected hose for returns to trip tank.

SLB prepared primary and backup tools on deck for W/L run #3 USIT/CBL.

SLB tested primary and backup tools on deck.
Calibrated depth sensors.
Installed sheaves.
Meanwhile performed weekly maintenance on fwd and aft PRS.
Installed new cladding on drag chain.
Cleaned and tieded rig floor.
Performed Pre-job Meeting for M/U toolstring and USIT/CBL run.

M/U BHA for run #3 (USIT/CBL).
Zeroed tool and checked toolstring at surface.
Opened SV and HMV.
RIH w/ run #3 from surface to 3039 m.
Logged USIT/CBL across interval 3040 - 2742 m. Performed two repeat passes across same interval.
Waited on confirmation from town on log data quality.
POOH from 2742 m to surface. Average pulling speed 20 m/min.
Closed HMV and SV. Broke and L/D run #3 USIT/CBL toolstring.

R/D SLB add-on cable from AWS unit.
Reconfigured AWS winch to run 5/16" e-line.
R/D pump-in sub with return hose.
M/U weight bars to cable head, stabbed lubricator and M/U same. Lined up to test riser and lubricator.
Tested lubricator and W/L riser to 20/200 bar for 5/10 min using the cement unit.
Flushed riser and lubricator with nitrogen back to trip tank.

SLB prepared toolstring on rig floor.
Rerouted lines to multibowl, lined up to test same.

P/U and M/U BHA for run #4 (tubing punch).
Tested annular line-up to 20/200 bar for 5/10 min. Pressured up annulus to 5 bar.

Opened HMV and SV. RIH w/ run #4 (tubing punch) from surface to 250 m.
Lifted barriers and powered up SLB unit.

Bled of lubricator pressure from 34 bar to 2 bar via closed drain. Closed KWV.
Verified ASV open on AWS local control panel.

Performed correlation pass across interval 2840 - 2700 m. Performed tie-in pass on same interval.
Positioned puncher with top shot at 2782 m. WHP 0 bar/ Annulus pressure 3 bar. Punched interval 2782 - 2785 m. Observed annulus pressure 28 bar.
POOH w/ run#4 from 2782 m to 250 m.
Made PA announcement and placed barriers. Powered down SLB unit.
POOH from 250 m into tool catcher. Closed HMV and SV.
Broke lubricator. L/D toolstring on deck. All guns fired.

Verified line-up for circulating tubing and annulus.

Staged up pumps and pumped 1,21 sg OBM with 1000 lpm/ 20 bar to FCP 100 bar. Pumped 65 m3.

Soft landed BOP on surface riser.

Checked cut distance with 400 lpm / 28 bar. 0,5 m cut.

100 rpm, 400 - 800 lpm, 5 - 8 kNm.
